ChangeLog

CURRENT TRUNK, TER version 0.2.1

TER version 0.2.0 (2015/02)
* bugfix: fix normal backlinkParams, see http://forge.typo3.org/issues/50818, thanks to Stano Paska
* feature: hook for generating backlinkParams, thanks to Stano Paska
* task: upload current trunk version to TER which is compatible with TYPO3 6.2
* bugfix: check if direct_mail is installed before changing values in the database related to direct_mail
* feature: add password strength meter, needs jquery (inclusion of jquery can be enablen in typoscript)
* bugfix: fix css which made passwort strength meter progress bar disappear under password input field
* bugfix: add missing label "reapeat password" in change password plugin (pi2)

TER version 0.1.6 (2013/09)
* security fix: clean hashes

TER version 0.1.5 (2013/09)
* bugfix: Fix Usage of deprecated php parameter is_dst in mktime(), see http://forge.typo3.org/issues/43669, thanks to Tilo Baller
* feature: send email to admin after registration, see http://forge.typo3.org/issues/41705, thanks to Marcus Schwemer
* feature: confirmation by administrator, every new registration has to be confirmed by an administrator (has to be enabled in typoscript)
* feature: added footer for mails, can be activated with plugin.tx_keuserregister.notification.addFooter = 1, adds a template subpart to emails

TER version 0.1.4 (2012/10)
* fixed broken documentation after rendering at typo3.org

TER version 0.1.3 (2012/10)
* documentation maintenance
* css inclusion changed for compatybility to TYPO3 6.0
* minor template and css improvements

TER version 0.1.2 (2012/08)
* bugfix: tstamp is not updated when updating fe_user record. Thanks to Marcus Schwemer (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/39620)
* bugfix: delete directmail mm entries after hook	
* moved birthday field funcs from ext_tables.php to external file. Thanks to Marcus Schwemer (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/34391)
* changelog moved from documentation to ChangeLog file in EXT dir
* added default notification sender email to static setup


TER version 0.1.1 (2012/06)
* removed deprecated function t3lib_div::int_from_ver
* bugfix: removed double definition of birthday fields from ext_tables.php, thanks to Marcus Schwemer and Jonas Götze (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/34391)
* bugfix: removed deprecated parameter for function mktime(...)


TER version 0.1.0 (2012/05)
* Confirmation hash added to notification markers, thanks to Jonas Götze (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/37164)
* absRefPrefix is checked when generating links for mails. If absRefPrefix is set, the Link does not get prefixed with TYPO3_SITE_URL, thanks to Michael Cannon (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/35396)
* New T3 mail api is used if T3 version is at least 4.5, older versions use the old T3 mail api (old mail api does not longer exist since T3 version), thanks to Jonas Götze (http://forge.typo3.org/issues/36498)
* bugfix: fields “first_name”, “last_name” and “gender” are not longer created with installing this extension. Since TYPO3 4.5 these fields are generated by the core system. Creating these fields again lead to errors so that the values can not be edited in backend.
* optimization: summarized error message for “date of birth” fields instead of single messages for each field
* New field type “Day of birth as dropdown”, thanks to Tanel Põld
* Default labels for “date of birth” dropdowns added
* CSS improvements (checkboxes, date of birth)
* bugfix: multiple checkbox values are handled as bit values now
* salutation based on gender, first_name and last_name added to edit form
* Changed position of field “registerdate” in the backend to “after usergroup”.


TER version 0.0.5 (2010/09)
* Existance of method t3lib_div::removeXSS is checked from now; if it is not available an own copy of the RemoveXSS script delivered with this extension is used; this improves compatibility to older TYPO3 versions


TER version 0.0.4 (2010/09)
* sending success mail to user after confirming his registration is configurable by TYPOScript now (activated by default)
* bugfix: show correct error message when uploaded file is larger than allowed, thanks to Nadine Schwingler
* new feature: auto login after successful registration confirmation; configurable by TYPOScript (activated by default)
* new feature: generate backlink to “last visited page” at “confirmation successful” page; configurable by TYPOScript


TER version 0.0.3 (2010/09)
* new feature: password validation for numeric chars (“password must contain at least X numeric values”), thanks to Nadine Schwingler


TER version 0.0.2 (2010/09)
* documentation update


TER version 0.0.1 (2010/08)
* salted passwords support added
* hook for prefill values added
* bugfix: file ending comparison when uploading an image
* bugfix: email field values are trimmed now
* bugfix: do not exit processing if salted password is not activated in ts config
* sys_dmail_category removed from default config because of errors if directmail is not installed
